To reflect our assumption that changes in the status of one boundary affect but do not dominate the status of another, we chose values such that the sum of coefficients reflecting interactions affecting Biosphere integrity does not exceed 1/3. We further assume that a weak interaction is approximately an order of magnitude less than a strong interaction, so the interaction strength declines by a factor of 3 from strong to moderate and another factor of 3 from moderate to weak. These values reflect the extent of additional advance towards, or retreat from, transgression of one boundary caused by advance towards, or retreat from, transgression of another. In the original report, eight of the boundaries interact directly only with the ninth, Biosphere integrity. As this is a bidirectional interaction,indirect effects among boundary statuses arise through the effect of the total change in biosphere integrity status caused by changes in status of the other eight boundaries.\
